Integument:
Prodorsum, notogaster, ventral plate, anal plate, pedotectum I micropunctate. Coxisternum, lamella, pedotectum I, genal tooth, tutorium, mentum, anterior of pteromorph with striae and micropunctae (
Fig. 24
). Mentum with striae in fingerprint pattern (
Fig. 24E
). Genital plate micropunctate with strong striae (
Fig. 24D
).

Ventral Region:
Epimeral setae 6–27 µm long, barbed; 
3c
longest seta; 
4c
weakly barbed, shortest seta. Genital, aggenital, anal and adanal setae weakly barbed, about 8–10 µm long. Genital setae 2+4. Postanal porose area oval, about 17 x 7 µm.
